# Skill: Unit Tests for RuntimeError Precondition Guards

## Overview

| Field | Value |
| ------- | ------- |
| **Date** | 2026-02-27 |
| **Project** | ProjectScylla |
| **Objective** | Add unit tests covering all `if x is None: raise RuntimeError(...)` guards |
| **Outcome** | Success — 8 new tests pass, full suite 3265 passed, 78.42% coverage |
| **Issue** | HomericIntelligence/ProjectScylla#1144 |
| **PR** | HomericIntelligence/ProjectScylla#1210 |

## Key Patterns

- Single-guard: null the field, `pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=r"field")`.
- Multi-guard (parametrize): set all fields valid, null only the one under test.
- Runner-level guard: patch the method that sets the field as no-op, let guard fire.
- Closure guard: call builder, get closure dict, invoke `actions[Key]()` directly.
- Local-import rule: patch `defining_module.ClassName`, not `caller_module.ClassName`.

## Failed Attempts

| Attempt | What Was Tried | Why It Failed | Lesson Learned |
| --------- | ---------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| N/A | Direct approach worked | N/A | Solution was straightforward |
```

